sion principle $\\mathsf{COH}$, a strengthening of\n$\\mathsf{CRT}^2_2$, is never computably true in a model of $\\mathsf{RCA}^*_0$\nand, as a consequence, does not follow from $\\mathsf{RT}^2_2$ over\n$\\mathsf{RCA}^*_0$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 24 May 2021 10:30:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-05-25"}
