idate the complementary role played by\nendogenous chemotaxis and matrix degradation in the formation of clusters, and\nthey indicate that previous approaches to the nonlocal modelling of\ncell-to-cell adhesion, while they capture the aggregating effect of\ncell-to-cell adhesion, are not sufficient to capture its stabilising effect on\nclusters, and new continuum cell-adhesion modelling strategies are required.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 24 May 2021 11:58:04 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 4 Oct 2021 22:05:59 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 21 Mar 2022 18:27:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-23"}
